display="block"><![CDATA[   \epsilon ' x :\equiv    \epsilon   \mathopen {}\left \lparen f  \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {} \right \rparen \mathclose {} ^{-1} \cdot  \mathsf {act}_{f}  \mathopen {}\left \lparen \eta   \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {} \right \rparen \mathclose {}  \cdot  \epsilon  x  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>The coherence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon '\circ  f]]></fr:tex> can be constructed using our two naturality lemmas <fr:ref
addr="erct-001V"
href="erct-001V.xml"
taxon="Lemma" /> and <fr:ref
addr="erct-001W"
href="erct-001W.xml"
taxon="Lemma" />.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
